### ================================================================
### Smart Parking — Demand Prediction API Test Suite
### ================================================================
### Run with:
###   - VS Code REST Client extension
###   - Thunder Client
###   - curl (copy individual requests)
###
### Ensure backend is running: cd backend && node index.js
### ================================================================

@base = http://localhost:8000/api
@contentType = application/json

# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# 1. VALID PREDICTION REQUESTS
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

### 1a. POST /api/ai/demand/predict — Valid 5-hour prediction
POST {{base}}/ai/demand/predict
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "current_hour": 14,
  "horizon": 5
}

### Expected: 200, { success: true, data: { predictions: [...], confidence, version, metadata } }


### 1b. POST /api/ai/demand/predict — Single hour prediction
POST {{base}}/ai/demand/predict
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "current_hour": 8,
  "horizon": 1
}

### Expected: 200, predictions array with 1 element


### 1c. POST /api/ai/demand/predict — Full 24-hour prediction
POST {{base}}/ai/demand/predict
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "current_hour": 0,
  "horizon": 24,
  "history": {
    "parking_occupancy": [0.65, 0.70, 0.72, 0.68],
    "traffic_volume": [120, 150, 140, 130]
  }
}

### Expected: 200, 24 predictions with history influence


### 1d. POST /api/ai/demand/predict/daily — 24-hour forecast
POST {{base}}/ai/demand/predict/daily
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{}

### Expected: 200, 24 predictions, metadata.period = "24h"


### 1e. POST /api/ai/demand/predict/weekly — 7-day forecast
POST {{base}}/ai/demand/predict/weekly
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{}

### Expected: 200, 7 predictions, metadata.period = "7d"


# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# 2. HEALTH CHECK
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

### 2a. GET /api/ai/demand/health — Service health
GET {{base}}/ai/demand/health

### Expected: 200, { status, model_loaded, ai_available }


# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# 3. INVALID / MISSING FIELDS → 400
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

### 3a. POST /api/ai/demand/predict — Missing current_hour
POST {{base}}/ai/demand/predict
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "horizon": 5
}

### Expected: 400, { success: false, error: "current_hour (number, 0-23) is required" }


### 3b. POST /api/ai/demand/predict — Missing horizon (uses default)
POST {{base}}/ai/demand/predict
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "current_hour": 10
}

### Expected: 200, default horizon=5


# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# 4. INVALID TYPES → 400
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

### 4a. POST /api/ai/demand/predict — current_hour as string
POST {{base}}/ai/demand/predict
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "current_hour": "14",
  "horizon": 5
}

### Expected: 400, { success: false, error: "current_hour (number, 0-23) is required" }


### 4b. POST /api/ai/demand/predict — current_hour out of range
POST {{base}}/ai/demand/predict
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "current_hour": 25,
  "horizon": 5
}

### Expected: 400, { success: false, error: "current_hour must be between 0 and 23" }


### 4c. POST /api/ai/demand/predict — negative hour
POST {{base}}/ai/demand/predict
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "current_hour": -1,
  "horizon": 3
}

### Expected: 400


# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# 5. EDGE CASES
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

### 5a. POST /api/ai/demand/predict — Midnight (hour 0)
POST {{base}}/ai/demand/predict
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "current_hour": 0,
  "horizon": 3
}

### Expected: 200, low occupancy values (night profile)


### 5b. POST /api/ai/demand/predict — Peak hour (14:00)
POST {{base}}/ai/demand/predict
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "current_hour": 14,
  "horizon": 4
}

### Expected: 200, high occupancy values (> 0.6)


### 5c. POST /api/ai/demand/predict — Empty body
POST {{base}}/ai/demand/predict
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

### Expected: 400 (no current_hour)


# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# 6. BACKWARD COMPATIBILITY — Legacy endpoints
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

### 6a. POST /api/ai/predict — Legacy endpoint
POST {{base}}/ai/predict
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "hour": 10,
  "horizon": 3
}

### Expected: 200, { success: true, data: { prediction: [...], hours_ahead } }


### 6b. GET /api/ai/health — Legacy health endpoint
GET {{base}}/ai/health

### Expected: 200


# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# 7. INTEGRATION — Analytics Backend Endpoints
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

### 7a. GET /api/analytics/efficiency/slots — Live data efficiency
GET {{base}}/analytics/efficiency/slots

### Expected: 200, { occupancyPercentage, availableSlots, averageDurationMinutes, turnoverRate, utilizationScore }


### 7b. GET /api/analytics/efficiency — Mock efficiency
GET {{base}}/analytics/efficiency

### Expected: 200, mock area-level efficiency data
